# {{CMD_PREFIX}}-status

Model/effort: Haiku / low.

A read-only situational report. Makes no changes and opens no branches — it only
observes and summarizes the two state planes plus framework drift.

## Steps
1. Fetch and prune; read the latest `05-logs/` entry and the master index for context
   (read-only — this command performs no writeback).
2. Report the backlog: open issues by priority and which are claimed vs unclaimed.
3. Report open PRs and their CI status; flag anything red or stale.
4. Report brain health: capabilities map freshness, docs-mesh validity, active-agents
   registry.
5. Report framework-version drift: compare the brain manifest `framework_version`
   against the hub registry `brain-factory/registry/framework-version.json`; note if
   `{{CMD_PREFIX}}-upgrade` is due.
6. Summarize in a short status block. Make no commits.

## Done when
A concise status block covers backlog, PRs/issues, CI, brain health, and version
drift, with nothing written.
